# The neural-bridge has NO per-app .env — all of its config lives in the
# monorepo-root .env (loaded automatically via python-dotenv), alongside the
# rest of the project's environment.
#
# The bridge reads these from the root .env (see the comments there for values):
#   MUSE_ADDRESS               Bluetooth MAC of the Muse (run `python -m neural_bridge scan`)
#   REDIS_URL                  Redis to publish to (on Proxmox: the desktop's LAN IP)
#   BD_REDIS_CHANNEL_SAMPLES   pub/sub channel for sample + bands frames
#   BD_REDIS_CHANNEL_STATUS    pub/sub channel for status frames
#   MUSE_PRESET                streaming preset (ignored by the 2016 model)
#   BD_NOTCH_HZ                mains-hum notch frequency (60 NA / 50 elsewhere)
